Thanks for the Pull Request. Could you please add a test with test ecdsa certs?

Thanks for the test. Unfortunately, it does not cover the gRPC implementation of TLS which is done in the `ssl_transport_security.c` file. Sorry I should have been more specific :(. 

For testing, you have 2 choices.
1. do another end to end test with ecdsa certs (like `test/core/end2end/fixtures/h2_ssl.c`).
2. wait for a PR by @yihuazhang that will import some TSI (transport security) level unit tests which will make things much easier to test. 

If you're not in a hurry for this feature, I would recommend option 2.

Some of the failures are due to the fact the `boringssl` in third_party is not up to date with master and lacks an OpenSSL TLS compatibility sumbol as describe here:  https://boringssl.googlesource.com/boringssl/+/48e1d180a46b8caaf6b4619db07d078fb7cbcc60.

The symbol was dropped and then reintroduced, the version used by grpc master is in between, making some tests fail.

My recollection is that we are tracking the chromium branch of boringssl and it looks like the latest one has the fix: https://boringssl.googlesource.com/boringssl/+/chromium-stable/include/openssl/ssl.h#3851

@nicolasnoble, can we update?
Feel free to update the submodules in this pull request.

Sorry for the complicated flow but a few things here;
- We want to upgrade boring to the latest chromium-stable branch and not master.
- Looks like the sanity tests are not happy. At least you should clang-format your code.
- The new boringssl does not seem to compile (maybe you'll have better luck with the chromium-stable branch): https://grpc-testing.appspot.com/job/gRPC_pull_requests_linux/6817/testReport/junit/(root)/aggregate_tests/run_tests_c_linux_dbg_native/
